<subSubSection id="C368652E935A8E07F2AAF96DFBE7F8F6" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935A8E07F2AAF96DFBE7F8F6" blockId="3.[151,1436,1791,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935A8E07F2AAF96DFBE2F8F6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147345" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimen here recognized as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F01FF96DFD55F8D2" box="[546,644,1791,1817]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F1D0F96DFB9FF8D2" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" box="[1005,1102,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F1D0F96DFB9FF8D2" box="[1005,1102,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">cordatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m.”, “Hispania”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F371F8B1FE66F8F6" box="[332,439,1827,1853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F3E1F8B1FCEEF8F6" authority="Dejean, 1825" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" box="[476,831,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F3E1F8B1FD72F8F6" box="[476,675,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Ditomus cordatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F097F8B1FCEEF8F6" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[682,831,1826,1853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10584" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1825) Species general des coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome Premier. Crevot, Paris, xxx + 463 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8863" type="book" year="1825">Dejean, 1825</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935A8E07F18FF8B1FBF9F8F6" box="[946,1064,1827,1853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935A8E00F2FAF8D5FF3FFDD1" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="488" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935A8E07F2FAF8D5FDA3F83A" blockId="3.[151,1436,1791,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F2FAF8D5FEBAF8AA" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,363,1862,1889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10584" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1825) Species general des coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome Premier. Crevot, Paris, xxx + 463 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8863" type="book" year="1825">Dejean (1825)</bibRefCitation>
stated Puente del Arzobispo as the sampling locality which is in the westernmost part of the province of Toledo, in the southern Iberian Meseta. There are no details on the number and sex of the studied specimens, possibly because Dejean saw only one beetle. Thus, this specimen is recognized as the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935A8E07F688F81DFAC6F862" box="[1205,1303,1935,1961]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935A8E07F700F81DFF29F806" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935A8E07F700F81DFF29F806" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="487">Ditomus cordatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its characteristics fully agree with those mentioned in the original description and the current concept of the species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F31DF845FE66F83A" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[288,439,2007,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente, 1927</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935A8E07F3FCF845FDB4F83A" author="Antoine, M." box="[449,613,2006,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="487" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine, 1959</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2FAFF05FF03FE19" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
In the collection there are other specimens placed besides the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935D8E00F1BFFF05FC35FF7A" box="[898,996,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">holotype</typeStatus>
but none bear any label indicating that they were used by Dejean when writing the original description, nor show the words “Hispania” “Puente del Arzobispo”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F32BFF4DFEA6FF32" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" box="[278,375,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ditomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F32BFF4DFEA6FF32" box="[278,375,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">cordatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mihi”, etc. The species was placed within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F1EEFF4DFBE6FF32" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1830" box="[979,1079,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F1EEFF4DFBE6FF32" box="[979,1079,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Carterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F692FF4DFAA9FF32" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1906" box="[1199,1400,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tschitscherinellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F692FF4DFAA9FF32" box="[1199,1400,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Tschitscherinellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F2AAFE91FECFFED6" author="Csiki, E." box="[151,286,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref10369" refString="Csiki, E. (1906) Cicindelidae, Carabidae. In: Heyden von, L. F. J. D., Reitter, E. &amp; Weise, J. (Eds.), Catalogus Coleopterorum Europae, Caucasi et Armeniae Rossicae. Editio secunda. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, pp. 1 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1906">Csiki (1906</bibRefCitation>
: p. 60). No other taxon was included in this subgenus and thus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F1E7FE91FA91FED6" authority="Dejean, 1825" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1825" box="[986,1344,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F1E7FE91FB74FED6" box="[986,1189,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Carterus cordatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F691FE91FA91FED6" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[1196,1344,258,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref10584" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1825) Species general des coleopteres, de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome Premier. Crevot, Paris, xxx + 463 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8863" type="book" year="1825">Dejean, 1825</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
became the type species of the subgenus by monotypy. No criteria were indicated by Csiki to erect the new subgenus. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F75CFEB5FEFFFEAE" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tschitscherinellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F75CFEB5FEFFFEAE" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Tschitscherinellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been ranked either as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F139FED9FCB9FEAE" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1830" box="[772,872,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F139FED9FCB9FEAE" box="[772,872,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Carterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F18FFED9FBE6FEAE" author="Csiki, E." box="[946,1079,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref10369" refString="Csiki, E. (1906) Cicindelidae, Carabidae. In: Heyden von, L. F. J. D., Reitter, E. &amp; Weise, J. (Eds.), Catalogus Coleopterorum Europae, Caucasi et Armeniae Rossicae. Editio secunda. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, pp. 1 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1906">Csiki, 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F678FED9FB08FEAE" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[1093,1241,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente, 1927</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F737FED9FA4DFEAE" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1835" box="[1290,1436,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F737FED9FA4DFEAE" box="[1290,1436,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Odontocarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F2E8FEFDFEA8FE42" author="Antoine, M." box="[213,377,366,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine, 1959</bibRefCitation>
; Machado, 1992), or as genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F0EAFEFDFCA1FE42" author="Stichel, W." box="[727,880,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="209 - 242" refId="ref12442" refString="Stichel, W. (1923) Zur Phylogenesis eines geologisch jungen Formenkreises der Kafer, der Ditominen (Carab. Harpal.). Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 18, 209 - 242." type="journal article" year="1923">Stichel, 1923</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F1BEFEFDFBCAFE42" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[899,1051,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="931 - 964" refId="ref12478" refString="Wrase, D. W. (1994) Revision der Carterus angustus-Gruppe und Bemerkungen zur Gattung Carterus Dejean (Col., Carabidae, Harpalini). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 26, 931 - 964." type="journal article" year="1994">Wrase (1994)</bibRefCitation>
considered that 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F6EEFEFDFA4DFE42" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1906" box="[1235,1436,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tschitscherinellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F6EEFEFDFA4DFE42" box="[1235,1436,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Tschitscherinellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has morphological peculiarities that justify its ranking as genus. A key to this species is provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F73BFE01FF1FFE19" author="Wrase, D. W." pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">Wrase (2011: 163)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2FAFE49FF3FFDD1" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
It currently includes two polytypic species distributed in the Mediterranean and the Levant (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F6E4FE49FF33FDD1" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="1810" refId="ref11655" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 b) Subtribe Ditomina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 509 - 514." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
